Package: poxchat
Architecture: any
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 poxchat-common (= ${source:Version}),
 ${shlibs:Depends},
 ${misc:Depends},
Recommends:
 poxchat-plugin-fishlim,
 poxchat-plugin-sysinfo,
Suggests:
 poxchat-lua,
 poxchat-perl,
 poxchat-python,
 poxchat-plugin-checksum,
Description: IRC client for the GNOME desktop (GTK4)
 PoxChat is a GTK4 IRC (Internet Relay Chat) client. It is a fork of
 HexChat, modernised on top of GTK4 with expanded IRCv3 support.
 .
 Features:
  * Multiple servers/channels in one window
  * SASL: PLAIN, EXTERNAL, SCRAM-SHA-1/256/512, OAUTHBEARER
  * TLS via OpenSSL
  * IRCv3 message-tags, batch, echo-message, labeled-response,
    server-time, account-tag, chghost, setname and more
  * SQLite-backed scrollback with zstd compression
  * DCC file transfer, configurable themes, /command aliases
  * Loadable plugins (Perl, Python, Lua) — install poxchat-perl,
    poxchat-python or poxchat-lua to enable scripting

Package: poxchat-common
Architecture: all
Multi-Arch: foreign
Depends:
 ${misc:Depends},
Recommends:
 poxchat,
Description: IRC client for the GNOME desktop (GTK4) - common files
 PoxChat is a GTK4 IRC client, forked from HexChat.
 .
 This package contains the architecture-independent data files
 (icons, desktop entry, AppStream metadata and translations) shared
 by the poxchat binary.

